node.text: Some of your favorite @TikTok creators are coming to @AirbnbExperiences. Go behind the scenes and learn their secrets of self-expression—right from home. Work out with @trevorbell, take better photos with @bonnierzm, make home videos with @itsthemcfarlands, dance with choreographer @arbengiga and more. Link in bio.

node.text: Happy Mother’s Day from Miami baker and @airbnbexperiences host, @laromibakery. Originally from Argentina, she’ll show you how to make traditional alfajores that are sure to sweeten up Mom’s day. For as beautiful as these dulce de leche sandwich cookies turn out, they’re surprisingly simple to make. Follow Romina’s foolproof recipe or join her Online Experience to make a sweet suite of Latin desserts. Link in bio.

node.text: Happy Mother’s Day from Nashville-based singer-songwriter and @airbnbexperiences host, @annebucklemusic. Follow Anne’s simple tricks for crafting a tune, or join her Online Experience for live instruction and melody-making. Link in bio.

node.text:
In March, @AirbnbExperiences hosts all over the world had to stop doing what they love—sharing their interests and passions with others. 
Over the past few weeks, they’ve offered ideas for how to continue hosting even while we’re apart. 
They’ve adapted recipes based on what’s in their pantries, turned living rooms into yoga studios, and choreographed dances for families at home.

Today we’re excited to announce that Airbnb Experiences are now online. You can take a flamenco class with Lidón in Madrid, participate in a tarot card reading with Mak in Austin, or visit a colony of penguins in Cape Town—all from home.

True to Airbnb Experiences in real life, Online Experiences are hosted by remarkable people and set in small groups. Alongside making a new dish, maybe you’ll make a new friend, too.

Thank you to our incredible hosts around the world. We’ll see you online soon —> link in bio.

node.title: Meet Homage Hospitality, the hosts who built the hotel they always wanted.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Captain Cook, Hawaii. May be an image of outdoors and tree.

node.text:
This off-grid house is surrounded by kukui nut and hau trees on a horse ranch away from the crowds.  A labor of love for Superhost Ze, it features private access to the Ka’awaloa Trail and is only 15 minutes from Kealakekua Bay, where you can hike down to some of the Big Island’s most spectacular snorkeling. 

Link in bio for lava tile floors and fresh papaya.

Photo: @hostwithkate

node.text:
The breeze off the bay will eventually call you out to sea for sailing or surfing. Until then, Superhost Yohann’s townhouse is the perfect base for exploring this old town in the shadow of an 1861 viaduct. And the wide-ranging Musée de Morlaix is just steps away.

Link in bio to follow the breeze. 

Video: @lamaisondesvignesmorlaix

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Ilhabela, Sao Paulo, Brazil. May be an image of outdoors and tree.

node.text:
The lap pool is inviting, but you’ll probably do more laps to and from all the beaches nearby—including one within a 5-minute walk. At lunchtime, head to Manäpani to dine with your toes in the sand. Every time you come home to Superhost Marta’s charming house, you’ll pass a little waterfall. 

Link in bio for island life.

Photo: @donossogosto

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Burke, Vermont. May be an image of tree and outdoors.

node.text:
Superhosts Alexis and Skeeter may have perfected the summer evening. Surrounded by a classic Vermont landscape (think cows across the road), their 1968 A-frame is also close to epic mountain biking trails and Lake Willoughby. After roasting the day’s farmstand finds on the fire, challenge your travel companions to late-night air hockey in the game room. 

Link in bio to claim your Northeast Kingdom. 

Photo: @cfunk44

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Albuquerque, New Mexico. May be an image of furniture and living room.

node.text:
Crystal and Stephen made the inside of their house as bright and refreshing as the mountain views from the balcony (which live up to the neighborhood’s name, Vista Magnifica). Head out for a sopaipilla burger from Casa de Benavidez, an Albuquerque Isotopes baseball game, or a concert at the historic El Rey. 

Link in bio for Southwest sunshine.

Photo: @bluffside_mountainviews_abq

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Maringá - Rio de Janeiro. May be an image of tree.

node.text:
At Superhost Victor’s country cottage, the sunlight is a constant invitation outdoors. Follow the sound of the Rio Preto through the forest and over a wooden bridge to find a natural swimming pool that’s bound to become your second living room. 

Link in bio to sink into nature.

Photo: @chale.luanova

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in East Wenatchee, Washington. May be an image of tree, twilight, sky and nature.

node.text:
Superhosts Dennis and Sharon’s garden suite includes two VIP seats above the Columbia River. It’s an ideal place to rest up for (or recover from) a summer concert at the Gorge Amphitheatre, or to just hang out and get to know this scenic town. Start with wood-fired pizza at the Pybus Public Market, just across the river.

Link in bio for riverside retreat. 

Photo: @peacefulgardengetaway

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Tasmania. May be an image of tree and outdoors.

node.text:
This updated farm cottage is perfectly situated to serve as a base for kayaking, dolphin spotting, and waterfall hikes. But Superhost Natalie’s homemade sourdough bread and marmalade—along with her chooks’ fresh eggs—have a way of bringing out the homebody in even the most adventurous guest.

Link in bio for Tassie tranquility.

Photo: @brissiebarb

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb on July 14, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: Now’s your chance to live like an Olympic gold medalist for a night at @scottiepippen’s Chicago-area home. Shoot hoops in the indoor gym, watch the @olympics from the home theater or sit back and relax in the sauna—the choice is yours. Bookings for these three one-night stays open on July 22 at 1pm EDT. Shoot your shot at the link in our bio.

node.text:
Tucked among desert oaks and ancient junipers, this solar-powered retreat feels much farther from civilization than it is. Guests say Superhosts Lindsey and Yoni have thought of everything, from a telescope for stargazing to telescoping forks for marshmallows.

Link in bio to count planets from the hot tub. 

Photo: @detringphotography 
@thegrahamresidence

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Virginia. May be an image of furniture and living room.

node.text:
After a day of exploring Shenandoah National Park (practically next door) or the nearby vineyards, come home to a golden-hour picnic in a lush field. A few days in Superhost Justin’s spacious house might leave you seeking out unspectacular places, just for variety. 

Link in bio for Blue Ridge beauty.

Photo: @greenwoodvista

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Airbnb in Bali. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Wayan’s bamboo masterpiece lets you sink into the rhythm of the rainforest. The beach and Ubud are each a short scooter ride away, but you might find yourself staying home to listen a while longer to the frogs singing and the Ayung River flowing by. 

Link in bio for tropical townhouse.

Photo: @aurahousebali
